This paper discusses object detection in videos and proposes a new metric to evaluate detection delay. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of various detectors, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also discusses the sensitivity of the metric, which is related to statistical learning (cs.LG). Furthermore, the paper discusses the application of the proposed metric in autonomous vehicle perception, which is related to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of video object detection, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
